          "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Quality of life</span></span></span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 18375,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">HDI</span></span></span></span></p>"
        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">A research team is conducting a study to assess the well-being of individuals in a large urban community. They are collecting various data points to evaluate both the subjective and objective aspects of well-being. Which of the following data points would primarily assess a subjective component of well-being?</span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q5640861",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 34055,
      "difficulty_level": "intermediate",
      "subjects_id": [
        7
      ],
      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ans. C. Quality of life</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option C:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">The <strong>subjective component</strong> of <strong>well-being</strong> (as expressed by each individual) is referred to as <strong>&ldquo;quality of life&rdquo;.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Explanation</span></u></strong><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option A. Standard of living</span></strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">: Objective Component. <strong>WHO</strong> includes&nbsp;<strong>Income &amp; Occupation</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>Standards of housing</strong>, <strong>sanitation &amp; nutrition</strong>, and <strong>level of provision of health</strong>, educational, recreational &amp; other services, within this component. The standard&nbsp;of living depends on &lsquo;<strong>Per capita GNP&rsquo;.</strong>&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option B. Level of living</span></strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">:&nbsp; An objective Component. The most important <strong>indicator&nbsp;to assess level of living</strong> is <strong>IMR</strong>.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option D. HDI</span></strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">: <strong>Human Development Index</strong> is a <strong>composite index</strong> comprising of <strong>3 dimensions</strong>:&nbsp;<strong>Knowledge</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>Income</strong> and&nbsp;<strong>Longevity</strong>.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Educational Objective</span></u></strong><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">WHO Concept of Well-being</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Objective component</span></strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">: Standard of living, Level of living</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Subjective component</span></strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">: Quality of life</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ref</span></u></strong><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">: Park 26th ed, pg 16.</span></strong></span></span></p>",
